      "raw_text": "'.Dick' Hutchinson and other prop\nerty owners have complained to\nthe city commissioners against the\nstreet car tracks of the Washington\nWater Power company on Fifth ave-\nnue. near Arthur street. Mr.. Hutch\ninson charges that the tracks at that\npoint are IA inches above the grade\nlevel of the street.\n\n\nIn as much as the street was\nGtade0 long ago and it would cost\nA60 per wagon load to fill in with\nearth and gravel the commissioners\nare much perplexed about the matter.\n1t may reach the city council later.\n\n\nComplaint has also been made that\nthe city has not followed the curb\nline in sidewaiking at this point. but\nhave sidewalked around projecting\nrocks and around big boulders that\nlay inside the sidewalk line."
